evaluating only subjects having caesarean deliveries or those from ethnic
populations known to have a high prevalence of ultra-rapid metabolizers. Although
genotyping to guide pharmacotherapy was not cost saving, the cost to avert an
infant adverse event may represent good value for money in specific populations.
